******
[1] Damping off - Kansas
Date: Tue 28 Jun 2011
Source: AgFax [edited]
http://agfax.com/Content/kansas-soybeans-affected-by-damping-off-disease-this-year-06282011.aspx


_Pythium_ damping off disease has been rampant on soybeans this
spring [2011] throughout eastern and central Kansas. _Pythium_ is most
active on soybeans that emerge into cool, wet soils. Producers in
eastern and central Kansas who planted their soybeans in mid-May ran
into this problem in many cases.

Certain fungicide seed treatments will help protect against _Pythium_
for about 10-14 days. But if the disease pressure is high enough,
_Pythium_ can overwhelm the seed treatment.

[byline: Steve Watson, Kansas State University]

